kernelcraft (2.0) lunar; urgency=medium

  * New version 2.0:
    - merge virtme into kernelcraft
    - virtme: make sure all the kvm guest configs are enabled
    - configkernel: drop additional configs by default
    - run: introduce --append option
    - ppc64: Use pseries defconfig
    - riscv64: print cmdline size warning without blocking

 -- Andrea Righi <andrea.righi@canonical.com>  Thu, 27 Apr 2023 09:47:33 +0200

kernelcraft (1.9) lunar; urgency=medium

  * New version 1.9:
    - run: automatically enable --build-host-vmlinux on ppc64
    - run: Add new --compiler argument
    - config: support single config file and new config folder
    - setup: Fallback to /etc/kernelcraft.conf file .config doesn't exists
    - run: fix missing f-string in error message
    - setup: Install kernelcraft.conf and update the references
    - setup: Add argcomplete as dependency
    - setup: Create version.py to avoid missing package problems on install
    - config: introduce default_opts keyword to the config file
    - config: drop test git repo 'arighi-rust'
    - config: drop /etc/kernelcraft.conf and always use config in $HOME

